                            <comment id="238313" author="adilger" created="Mon, 10 Dec 2018 17:50:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;These failures are caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11366&quot; title=&quot;replay-single timeout test 80f: rm: cannot remove &amp;#39;/mnt/lustre/d80f.replay-single/remote_dir&amp;#39;: Input/output error&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11366&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11366&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so they will be gone when that problem is fixed.  The failures can all be annotated as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11366&quot; title=&quot;replay-single timeout test 80f: rm: cannot remove &amp;#39;/mnt/lustre/d80f.replay-single/remote_dir&amp;#39;: Input/output error&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11366&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11366&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in Maloo. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think there is anything else that needs to be done here.  We want the later tests to report a failure if they cannot clean up properly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
